biography_text: WALZ, Tim, a Representative from Minnesota; born in West Point, Cuming County, Nebr., April 6, 1964; graduated from Butte High School, Butte, Nebr.; B.S., Chadron State College, Chadron, Nebr., 1989; M.S., Minnesota State University, 2001; attended Saint Mary’s University of Minnesota, Winona, Minn.; Nebraska National Guard, 1981-1996; Minnesota National Guard, 1996-2005; teacher; elected as a Democrat to the One Hundred Tenth and to the five succeeding Congresses (January 3, 2007-present).
